==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*bēō'', from Indo-European ''*bhī-''.  Germanic cognates include Old Frisian [[be|bē]], Middle Low German [[bie|bīe]] (Dutch [[bij]]), Old High German [[bia|bīa]], [[bini]] (German [[Biene]], dialectal [[Beie]]), Old Norse [[bý]] (Swedish [[bi]]).  The IE root is also the source of Lithuanian [[bite|bìtė]], Latvian [[bite]], Old Church Slavonic [[бьчела]] (Russian [[пчела]]), Celtic ''*beko-'' (Old Irish [[bech]], Irish [[beach]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /be:o/

